OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F163A1774015869
OL,1,Wj5hw1~{4k7juhw1{$             G2/2
OL,2,W+.-'"-$/*%*%*%/"-$/*%Q,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,3,GUK long range forecast
OL,4,
OL,5,COutlook for Fri 3 Apr to Fri 17 Apr
OL,6,FBlocked or slowly evolving weather
OL,7,Fpatterns are favoured during the first
OL,8,Fweek or so of April. High pressure is
OL,9,Fthe preferred flavour of this block;
OL,10,Fthis probably centred to the north or
OL,11,Fwest of the UK. This means plenty of
OL,12,Fdry weather, possibly with some
OL,13,Fpleasantly warm days, but an ongoing
OL,14,Fchance of overnight fog and frost.
OL,15,FMoving further into April, there is an
OL,16,Fincreasing chance that high pressure
OL,17,Fwill become less dominant and thus a
OL,18,Fgreater chance of more places seeing
OL,19,Fsome rain and possible stronger winds
OL,20,Ffrom time to time. Overall,
OL,21,Ftemperatures panning out somewhere
OL,22,Fnear to average.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
